  <h2 class="sec-title" id="weatherTitle">When to Visit <em>Karnataka</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="weatherNote" style="margin-bottom:0">Karnataka has three distinct climate zones: the Western Ghats (heavy monsoon, cool year-round), the Deccan Plateau (hot dry summers, mild winters) and the Coastal belt (hot and humid). October to March is ideal for Hampi, Mysuru and Bengaluru. The Western Ghats are most spectacular during and just after monsoon — July to October. Coorg is beautiful year-round.</p>
