{emoji:"🐘",name:"Mysuru Dasara",location:"Mysuru — October",desc:"India's most spectacular state festival — 10 days of celebration culminating on Vijayadashami. The Mysore Palace is illuminated by 100,000 bulbs every evening; the procession on the 10th day brings 12 decorated elephants bearing the golden howdah through city streets watched by one million people. Torchlight parade, cultural programs, wrestling competitions and the symbolic burning of Ravana. The Nada Habba of Karnataka."},
