{emoji:"🎊",name:"Ugadi — Kannada New Year",location:"Statewide — March/April",desc:"The Kannada and Telugu New Year — celebrated with the preparation of Ugadi Pachadi, a dish mixing six tastes (sweet, sour, bitter, salty, pungent and astringent) to represent life's full spectrum of experiences. New clothes, temple visits, mango leaf toranas at every door and the reading of Panchanga (almanac) predictions for the year. The most personally important festival in every Kannadiga household."},
{emoji:"🪔",name:"Hampi Utsav",location:"Hampi, Vijayanagara — November",desc:"A three-day cultural festival at the ruins of Hampi — classical and folk performances on the stone stages of the Vijayanagara ruins, lit by torchlight at night. Dancers perform against the Vittala Temple backdrop; Yakshagana troupes perform through the night; musicians from across South India gather. The combination of ancient ruins and living performance creates an experience of extraordinary power."},
